node.text:
We met Bailey back in 2017 at St. Jude™️ when he was undergoing treatment for osteosarcoma. It was so special for Chip and I to catch up with him this week and see how much he’s grown——and that he’s cancer-free! 

Click the button in my profile to donate to @stjude. #ChipInForStJude

node.text:
Whenever I'm needing creative inspiration for what to cook, I always start with the most basic ingredients. Maybe a simple herb or whatever is growing in the garden that season. Then I reach for a cookbook or go online for ideas and build the meal from there. There's an actual mental shift that happens—I go from feeling like I'm in a creative slump to all of a sudden enjoying a creative process that brings me joy. 

Yesterday, I woke up thinking about basil (and cheesecake), so I grabbed my cookbooks, looked for any recipe that included basil, and just went for it. 

These are always the moments that feel like an unexpected gift—simple and small but oftentimes the most fulfilling✨

node.text:
We had the loveliest day with @elizabethpoett and her family on their incredible ranch. Everything about it was a dream. We are leaving feeling full and completely inspired. ✨

Her series #RanchtoTable starts streaming this Friday on @magnolianetwork and @discoveryplus!
